==English==
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{AU}} A type of [[melon]], ''[[w:Cucumis melo reticulatus|Cucumis melo reticulatus]]'', with sweet orange flesh and a rough skin resembling netting.  Also known as [[cantaloupe]].

===Usage notes===
In Australia, this [[fruit]] (''C. m. reticulatus'') is known as rockmelon in [[Queensland]] and [[New South Wales]], but as [[cantaloupe]] in [[Victoria]].  (One of relatively few regional variations in terminology within Australia other than from commercial [[brand]]s).